{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1c5605ee-d482-47b4-89b1-f14c3c067479","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9, so you have full async lifecycle support. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; set; } = null!;\n\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // One-time async setup (shared across all tests in class)\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task TestInit()\n    {\n        // Per-test async setup; TestContext is already set here\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task TestCleanup()\n    {\n        // Per-test async teardown\n    }\n\n    [ClassCleanup]\n    public static async Task ClassTeardown()\n    {\n        // One-time async teardown\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        TestContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\nKey points for MSTest v3:\n\n- **`TestContext`** — declare as a settable property; the framework injects it automatically before `[TestInitialize]`.\n- **Async lifecycle** — `[TestInitialize]`, `[TestCleanup]`, `[ClassInitialize]`, and `[ClassCleanup]` all support `async Task` return types.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** receives its own `TestContext` parameter (static context); your instance property is separate and available per-test.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5b11bf36-0088-47cd-8305-cc48a2b44781","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use a property `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` — MSTest automatically sets it before each test runs. In MSTest 3.x, you can also inject it via constructor if using the newer patterns, but the property approach is the classic and still-recommended way.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[ClassInitialize]` (static) and `[TestInitialize]` (instance) methods.\n\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: In MSTest v3+, both `[TestInitialize]` and `[ClassInitialize]` can return `Task` for async support, and `[ClassInitialize]` accepts `TestContext` as a parameter.\n\nLet me give them a clear, concise answer about the modern recommended patterns with a practical example.","outputTokens":718,"requestId":"67C5:2ED2CA:2AE3487:2F8EC58:69FD3F77"},"id":"c3fd6a6e-5d7d-48ab-a164-978b1df31497","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:42:29.967Z","parentId":"e2dc834b-c772-4660-a1c9-0be96359d972"}
